8)\"/>\n\n    <meta name=\"citation_reference\" content=\"citation_title=A Guide to Usability&#8212;Human Factors in Computing; citation_publication_date=1994; citation_id=CR50; citation_author=J Preece; citation_publisher=Addison Wesley &amp; Open University\"/>\n\n    <meta name=\"citation_reference\" content=\"citation_title=Design meets disability; citation_publication_date=2009; citation_id=CR51; citation_author=G Pullin; citation_publisher=The MIT Press\"/>\n\n    <meta name=\"citation_reference\" content=\"Pullin, G.: When fashion meets discretion. (Awarded Best Full Paper) Include 2007, Royal College of Art, 1&#8211;4 April (2007a)\"/>\n\n    <meta name=\"citation_reference\" content=\"Pullin, G.: Social mobiles and speaking chairs: applying critical design to disorder and disruption, discourse and disability. European Academy of Design, Izmir, Turkey, 11&#8211;13 April (2007b)\"/>\n\n    <meta name=\"citation_reference\" content=\"Pullin, G.: I can&#8217;t talk now and other design stories: four assistive technologies for people with and without disabilities. In: Keates, S., Langdon, P., Clarkson, P.J., Robinson, P. (eds.) Universal Access and Assistive Technology. Springer, Heidelberg (2002)\"/>\n\n    <meta name=\"citation_reference\" content=\"Pullin, G.: Inclusion, inspriation and lightness of touch. In: Clarkson, J., Coleman, R., Keates, S., Lebbon, C. (eds.) Inclusive Design for the Whole Population, pp. 558&#8211;564. Springer, Heidelberg (2003)\"/>\n\n    <meta name=\"citation_reference\" content=\"Pullin, G., Newell, A.F.: Focussing on extra-ordinary users. In: HCI 2007, Beijing, 23&#8211;25 July 2007. Lecture Notes in Computer Science, 4554, vol. 5, pp. 253&#8211;262. Springer, Heidelberg (2007)\"/>\n\n    <meta name=\"citation_reference\" content=\"Pruitt, J., Grudin, J.: Personas: practice and theory. In: Proceedings of DUX 2003, CD ROM, 15 (2003)\"/>\n\n    <meta name=\"citation_reference\" content=\"citation_journal_title=Behav. Inf. Technol.;